Reference-contexts: We will focus here on binary CSPs, where constraints specify pairs of allowable values. Abstraction and reformulation are fundamental, powerful ideas in artificial intelligence, but they have not had a great deal of application in the area of constraint satisfaction (see <ref> [ Ellman, 1993; Nadel, 1990 ] </ref> for recent important exceptions). The obvious way to implement abstraction in a constraint satisfaction context is to simplify the problem by removing constraints, and then use the solutions to the simplified problem to guide the search for a solution to the original problem.
